93
00:06:20,540 --> 00:06:23,360
GDP, gross domestic products.

94
00:06:23,360 --> 00:06:35,480
That might seem confusing because gross means different things at different times, but in this case, domestic means our country, so within a country, all of the products add it up together.

95
00:06:36,720 --> 00:06:43,120
And gross is basically that, just all the products added up together without taking into consideration any other things.

96
00:06:43,579 --> 00:06:48,360
So the GDP is basically all the goods and services produced in a country within a given time.

97
00:06:48,920 --> 00:06:50,500
And what about per capita though?

98
00:06:51,019 --> 00:06:58,579
So per capita comes from Latin, per means four or each, and capita is a head, so this is per person.

99
00:06:59,079 --> 00:07:06,519
So GDP per capita means how much, how many goods and services are made divided by the number of people in that place.

100
00:07:07,439 --> 00:07:07,740
Exactly.

101
00:07:07,959 --> 00:07:15,220
So you probably have these indicators in your country or your own language as well, but that's basically it.

102
00:07:15,240 --> 00:07:18,000
And the acronym is gross domestic product.

103
00:07:18,000 --> 00:07:29,899
And just to explain a little bit, if you see this in Wikipedia or in an encyclopedia, normally a very low GDP per capita is $500, American dollars, and a high one would be $35,000.

104
00:07:30,379 --> 00:07:30,740
$35,000, yeah.

105
00:07:30,959 --> 00:07:32,300
And that's usually per year, right?

106
00:07:32,540 --> 00:07:35,959
Because that's usually how it's taken into consideration.

107
00:07:36,160 --> 00:07:37,240
The time is a year.

